# Translation Filename Conventions

- Theme translation files (`.po` and `.mo`) must use language-only filenames, such as `ar.po`, `ar.mo`, `en_US.po`, `en_US.mo`.
- Do not use theme text-domain-prefixed filenames like `zskeleton-ar.po` or `zskeleton-en_US.mo`.
- Plugin translation files (`.po` and `.mo`) must use `text-domain-language`, such as `woocommerce-ar.po`, `akismet-en_US.mo`.
- For plugins, always keep the text domain prefix to match WordPress plugin translation loading conventions.

## Examples

- Theme: `languages/ar.po` and `languages/ar.mo` (correct)
- Theme: `languages/zskeleton-ar.po` and `languages/zskeleton-ar.mo` (incorrect)
- Plugin: `languages/my-plugin-ar.po` and `languages/my-plugin-ar.mo` (correct)
